This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) as it deals with the task of fine-grained entity type classification using a neural network model that composes representations of entity mention contexts. Additionally, the paper also investigates the behavior of the attention mechanism of the model, which is a common technique used in NLP. 

The paper could also belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) as it proposes a novel neural network architecture for the task. 

Other possible sub-categories include Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) as the paper deals with a task that involves understanding and processing natural language, and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) as the model proposed is a neural network. 

Information Retrieval (cs.IR) could also be a possible sub-category as the task of entity type classification is related to information retrieval and organization.
